Add specs to test for empty search results

Fix undefined map error when zero foods are returned from search

For a food.search query that returns zero results, iterating over the
result set and attempting to create new Food objects yields the error:

`NoMethodError: undefined method 'map' for nil:NilClass`

This is fixed by only building the new Food objects if the result set
is populated with foods.

Make checking and pulling from Github optional

In order to test in isolation without a dependency on a network
connection or having to set a proxy (if behind a corporate firewall)
to reach Github, make checking and pulling from Github optional. Add
an :edge attribute (default true) to retain current functionality.
